<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="1034" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1034">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/19778</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Collector <persName type="to">Cobb</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-09T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1916, 6, p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Inform British Consul at Chihuahua British Embassy here has received his
                            message regarding situation in Chihuahua City, and desires him to know
                            that inasmuch as the Consul is on the spot, he is the best judge as to
                            what action to take to safeguard British subjects. Department of State
                            wishes British Consul to advise Americans to leave Chihuahua City.</p>
                        <p>Endeavor convey foregoing by trustworthy traveler, if possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>